    - target: {fileID: 2086081743145107749, guid: 7ffcca573e1296d47a9191342db0701b,
        type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_text
      value: 'L<sub>Surface</sub> = Light emitted from the surface [W / (sr  m2)]

        L<sub>e</sub>
        = Emissive light from the surface [W / (sr  m2)]

        L<sub>r</sub> =
        Reflected light from the surface [W / (sr  m2)]


        In the physical
        world, surfaces can only be seen when they interact with light. They can
        either emit light themselves or reflect light from a different source.

        The
        total light at the surface is the sum of these two.


        When just outputting
        the value red, the surface is essentially emitting red light while not interacting
        with the environment light at all.'
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 2086081743145107749, guid: 7ffcca573e1296d47a9191342db0701b,
        type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_fontSizeBase
      value: 0.03
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 2453436135830993782, guid: 7ffcca573e1296d47a9191342db0701b,
        type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_AnchorMax.y
      value: 0
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
